03870nam a22005175i 9780231556286DE-B159720240306123113.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20232023nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802315562867 a10.7312/blac206022doi  a(DE-B1597)679661  a(OCoLC)1409657293  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 4aBL1238.52b.B58 2024 7aLIT0240602bisacsh04a181/.45223/eng/202309141 aBlack, Shameem, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aFlexible India :bYoga's Cultural and Political Tensions /cShameem Black. 1aNew York, NY : bColumbia University Press, c[2023] 4c©2023  a1 online resource  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tAcknowledgments -- tNote on Transliteration -- tPROLOGUE: THE BRACELET -- t1 SETTING UP: YOGA’S FLEXIBLE FORMS -- t2 CONDUCTING MASS PRACTICE: INDIA’S VISION FOR YOGA -- t3 ALIGNING BOTH HANDS: YOGA IN INDIAN FICTION -- t4 ASSUMING CORPSE POSE: YOGA IN U.S. POPULAR CULTURE -- t5 BENDING OVER BACKWARD: YOGA’S PRECARIOUS WORK -- t6 FRAMING NEW PARTS: YOGA THROUGH DIASPORIC CRITIQUE -- t7 LYING OUT: SPECTRAL YOGA -- tEPILOGUE: THE MOON -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aYoga has offered the Indian state unprecedented opportunities for global, media-savvy political performance. Under Modi, it has promoted yoga tourism and staged mass yoga sessions, and Indian officials have proposed yoga as a national solution to a range of social problems, from reducing rape to curing cancer. But as yoga has gone global, its cultural meanings have spiraled far and wide. In Flexible India, Shameem Black travels into unexpected realms of popular culture in English from India, its diaspora, and the West to explore and critique yoga as an exercise in cultural power.Drawing on her own experience and her readings of political spectacles, yoga murder mysteries, court cases, art installations, and digital media, Black shows how yoga’s imaginative power supports diverse political and cultural ends. Although many cultural practices in today’s India exemplify “culture wars” between liberal and conservative agendas, Flexible India argues that visions of yoga offer a “culture peace” that conceals, without resolving, such tensions. This flexibility allows states, corporations, and individuals to think of themselves as welcoming and tolerant while still, in many cases, supporting practices that make minority populations increasingly vulnerable. However, as Black shows, yoga can also be imagined in ways that offer new tools for critiquing hierarchical structures of power and race, Hindu nationalism, cultural appropriation, and self-help capitalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aYogaxSocial aspects2DLC. 0aYogaxSocial aspects. 0aYogazIndia2DLC. 0aYogazIndia. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Modern / 21st Century .2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/blac2060240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231556286423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231556286/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles